		<h3>Irony</h3>
		<p>
			Fred Gijbels’s works are full of absurd and irony, however, what also breathes from this is the feeling of being encircled. 
			The author notices the omnipresence of ideology that penetrates the simplest daily activities, consumer or even culinary choices, 
			is dominated by references to politics, belief systems and the twentieth – century ideologies that were supposed to bring humanity 
			worldly salvation, worldly paradise.
		</p>
		
